===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|i}} вҖ“ a man with a mask ({{zh-l|*з”°}}) over his face. Possible interpretations:
* Strange, bizarre вҖ” "uncommon".
* Different face вҖ” "different".

Compare {{zh-l|*й¬ј|demon}}, where the {{lang|zh|з”°}} also derives from a face or a mask. Compare also [[зҰә]], in which the top component represents either a mask or a monkey's face.

Alternatively, may be a {{liushu|p|nocap=y}} of a person carrying something on his head, the original form of {{zh-l|*жҲҙ|to carry on the head}}.

Modern form is graphically {{Han compound|з”°|е…ұ}}, though this is not the etymology.

